OL,6,FShe added: "One of the things that, in
OL,7,Fspite of everything, I like about the
OL,8,FBritish honour system is the way it
OL,9,Frecords people who do very low
OL,10,Fprofile, working for free, long hours,
OL,11,Fweeks, months, years, for something
OL,12,Fthat they genuinely believe in and
OL,13,Fusually unpaid, and for the benefit of
OL,14,Fother people, and they are the bedrock
OL,15,Fof the honour system, and they
OL,16,Factually are the reason why it is so
OL,17,Frespected, and knights and dames are
OL,18,Fjust cherries on the top of that cake.
OL,20,F"I am happy to be a cherry."
