OL,6,F"My stepfather, for example, was in
OL,7,Fthe trenches at 15, my grandfather had
OL,8,Fa bayonet wound, and he used to get
OL,9,Fstripped off at the kitchen sink, and
OL,10,Fthe bayonet wound was terrible, very
OL,11,Fobvious, and he never talked about it.
OL,12,FSo you've got the two things there
OL,13,Fthat are essential for writers, a
OL,14,Fstory that is obviously present, but
OL,15,Fwhich isn't being told.
OL,17,F"The last thing any writer needs is a
OL,18,Fcompleted story. What you need as a
OL,19,Fwriter is a mystery. And I had that."
