OL,6,F"I think that is a battle that is
OL,7,Fstill being fought for women in lots
OL,8,Fof ways. And that shadows the
OL,9,Fsubsequent lives of women, but also of
OL,10,Ftheir children, who are very often the
OL,11,Fproduct of rape, and that is difficult
OL,12,Ffor the woman and the child and the
OL,13,Fcommunity that the woman comes from.
OL,15,F"So it seems as if it's thousands of
OL,16,Fyears ago but actually myth isn't
OL,17,Fthousands of years ago. Myth is
OL,18,Fapplicable to our lives today, and
OL,19,Fthat's always what I want to bring
